							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">2</span>
								<p><strong>Gas Valve Opens:</strong> The gas valve opens, allowing natural gas or propane to flow to the
									burners.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">3</span>
								<p><strong>Ignition:</strong> The ignition system lights the gas, creating flames in the burner
									assembly.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">4</span>
								<p><strong>Heat Exchanger:</strong> The flames heat the metal heat exchanger, which becomes hot.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">5</span>
								<p><strong>Air Circulation:</strong> The blower motor pushes air across the hot heat exchanger, warming
									the air.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">6</span>
								<p><strong>Distribution:</strong> The warm air is distributed throughout your home via the ductwork.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">7</span>
								<p><strong>Exhaust:</strong> Combustion byproducts are vented outside through the flue pipe.</p>
							</li>
